name: places/ChIJs3oprUQQ2jERp8A9mbkPZJE/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNUaE0tdHpnRRAB
text: {'text': "Bukit Batok Nature Park offers a serene escape from the urban bustle of Singapore. With lush greenery, tranquil walking trails, and picturesque quarry viewpoints, it's a haven for nature lovers and hikers alike. The park's highlight is the tranquil quarry pool, surrounded by towering cliffs and filled with clear water, perfect for a refreshing dip or a scenic picnic. The park also features well-maintained paths for jogging and cycling, making it a popular spot for outdoor enthusiasts. Its historical significance as a former granite quarry adds an intriguing layer to its beauty. However, some visitors may find the park's relatively small size limiting, especially if seeking extensive hiking opportunities. Overall, Bukit Batok Nature Park is a charming oasis that offers a peaceful retreat and a glimpse into Singapore's natural heritage.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJs3oprUQQ2jERp8A9mbkPZJE/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURiMUxPZ0F3EAE
text:
{'text': 'Free admission.
A Nature Park that is beautiful and also with some sad World War 2 history ( at the World War 2 Memorial Site ).
I like the Quarry Cliff and the pond is lively with plenty of fish and terrapins.

**Do note that some parts of the park are closed for maintenance until 31 December 2027.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJs3oprUQQ2jERp8A9mbkPZJE/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQyN3BXUFF3EAE
text:
{'text': 'A peaceful and tranquil park in the west side.
Great place for a leisure walk to enjoy the nature and best of all- it is free. You could enjoy the fresh air in the morning and enjoy natural scenery. You should be able to see some chicken or rooster along the way too.
The route was well maintained and clean, with ample bins along the route.
A great healthy family destination to visit, with something for everyone in the family.
Strongly recommended!!!', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJs3oprUQQ2jERp8A9mbkPZJE/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURfdDZmOWl3RRAB
text:
{'text': 'The park is a beautiful escape into nature, offering a tranquil and serene atmosphere that makes it perfect for a relaxing walk or simply unwinding.

The lush greenery and well-maintained trails were a pleasure to explore. Whether you’re an avid nature lover or just looking for a peaceful spot to refresh your mind, this park has something for everyone. The paths are easy to navigate and suitable for all fitness levels, making it a great destination for families, couples, or solo visitors.

One of the highlights is the park’s iconic quarry, which offers a scenic view that’s both calming and picturesque. It’s a wonderful spot to take in the beauty of nature or snap a few photos. The sound of birds and the rustling of leaves add to the park’s charm, making it a perfect retreat from the busy city life.

We truly appreciated the quietness and cleanliness of the park. It’s an ideal place for a morning walk, an afternoon hike, or even a peaceful moment of reflection. Bukit Batok Nature Park is undoubtedly worth a visit for anyone looking to connect with nature in a calm and refreshing setting.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
